2. Rye Chips in Soups: The Ultimate Garnish
Forget boring crackersâ€”rye chips are the perfect topping for soups. Their crispy texture holds up well against hot broth, adding both crunch and flavor.
Tomato Soup & Rye Chips
Pair the tangy sweetness of tomato soup with the deep, nutty flavor of rye chips. Instead of dipping a grilled cheese, try sprinkling crushed rye chips on top for a satisfying contrast.
Creamy Soups & Rye Chips
Cream-based soups like potato, mushroom, or cauliflower get an instant upgrade with a handful of rye chips. Their bold flavor cuts through the richness, adding a bit of complexity to each bite.
