If you love Eastern European flavors, try adding rye chips to a bowl of borscht. The ryeâ€™s slightly sour taste pairs beautifully with the beets and cabbage, making for an authentic, flavorful combo.
Pro Tip: If you like an extra-savory touch, drizzle some olive oil over your rye chips and toast them in the oven for a few minutes before adding them to soups.

