Breadcrumb Substitute
Crush rye chips into fine crumbs and use them as a substitute for breadcrumbs in meatballs, meatloaf, or even as a crispy coating for chicken or fish. The rye adds a deeper flavor than traditional breadcrumbs.
Dips & Spreads
Instead of regular crackers, use rye chips as dippers for hummus, spinach dip, or even a creamy cheese spread. Their sturdy texture makes them perfect for scooping up thick dips.
